(WOMAN VOCALISING)

00:43.293 --> 00:44.761
(BABY COOING)

00:46.463 --> 00:47.715
(VOCALISING CONTINUES)

00:47.798 --> 00:49.721
(SINGING) <i>You are my world</i>

00:49.800 --> 00:51.427
<i>My darling</i>

00:51.802 --> 00:55.727
<i>What a wonderful world I see</i>

00:56.306 --> 00:59.810
<i>You are the song I'm singing</i>

01:00.185 --> 01:06.989
<i>You're my beautiful Melody</i>

01:15.117 --> 01:16.960
<i>Darling we'd better be going</i>

01:17.035 --> 01:18.753
<i>Look at her, isn't she glowing</i>

01:18.829 --> 01:20.752
<i>She looks divine
and you look exquisite</i>

01:20.831 --> 01:23.084
<i>- But look at the time
- Couldn't be is it</i>

01:23.166 --> 01:25.089
<i>The crew is awaiting your orders</i>

01:25.168 --> 01:27.136
<i>We're sailing away from our borders</i>

01:27.212 --> 01:28.259
<i>Steady. boy, steady</i>

01:28.338 --> 01:29.430
Ahoy there! They're coming!

01:29.506 --> 01:31.474
Trumpeters ready!
Drummers, start drumming!

01:31.550 --> 01:33.177
(TRUMPETERS PLAY FANFARE)

01:35.137 --> 01:36.855
<i>Down to the sea we go</i>

01:36.930 --> 01:39.103
<i>Down to a world I know</i>

01:39.182 --> 01:41.105
<i>There's never been not ever before</i>

01:41.184 --> 01:43.061
<i>A child born of sea and shore</i>

01:43.145 --> 01:45.239
CREW: <i>Down to the sea we go</i>

01:45.314 --> 01:46.941
<i>Down to the world below</i>

01:47.024 --> 01:48.617
<i>A journey to bless a princess-to-be</i>

01:48.692 --> 01:50.285
<i>Under the sun</i>

01:50.360 --> 01:52.829
<i>And under the sea</i>

01:56.366 --> 01:57.583
<i>Ariel's coming</i>

01:57.659 --> 01:59.377
Ariel's coming?

02:00.162 --> 02:01.129
<i>Ariel's coming</i>

02:01.204 --> 02:02.672
- Ariel's coming?
- Ariel's coming?

02:02.748 --> 02:04.250
Ariel's coming?

02:04.333 --> 02:11.262
<i>- Ariel's coming
- Ariel's coming, Ariel's coming</i>

02:11.340 --> 02:12.933
<i>What's all the big commotion</i>

02:13.008 --> 02:14.385
<i>That's spreading through the ocean</i>

02:14.468 --> 02:16.470
<i>From sea to shining sea</i>

02:16.553 --> 02:17.554
(LAUGHS)

02:17.638 --> 02:19.481
<i>There is no hesitating</i>

02:19.556 --> 02:21.149
<i>Today we celebrating</i>

02:21.224 --> 02:22.897
<i>Ariel's Melody</i>

02:24.978 --> 02:28.403
<i>Today when Triton's daughter
comes back here to the water</i>

02:28.523 --> 02:30.571
<i>We gonna have a spree</i>

02:30.692 --> 02:31.784
Ha!

02:31.860 --> 02:33.737
<i>The boat is nearer now</i>

02:33.820 --> 02:38.075
<i>I think I hear her now
Ariel's Melody</i>

02:38.241 --> 02:40.289
CHORUS: <i>La-da, da-da, di-da-da</i>

02:40.369 --> 02:42.042
<i>- La-da, da-da, di-da-da
- Ohh-oh</i>

02:42.204 --> 02:45.003
- CHORUS: <i>La-da-di-daah</i>
<i>- Yeah</i>

02:45.248 --> 02:47.250
- CHORUS: <i>La, la-da, di-da-da</i>
<i>- La-la-la</i>

02:47.334 --> 02:51.305
- CHORUS: <i>La-da, di-da-da</i>
<i>- La-la-la La-la, la-la</i>

02:51.546 --> 02:53.423
MERPEOPLE: <i>Up from the sea we rise</i>

02:53.507 --> 02:55.259
<i>Up to the world of skies</i>

02:55.342 --> 02:57.140
<i>There's never been not ever before</i>

02:57.219 --> 02:58.971
<i>A child born of sea and shore</i>

02:59.054 --> 03:01.022
<i>Up from the sea we rise</i>

03:01.098 --> 03:02.771
<i>Up to the world of skies</i>

03:02.849 --> 03:05.523
<i>Forever to be together as one</i>

03:05.602 --> 03:07.821
<i>Under the sea</i>

03:07.896 --> 03:09.148
<i>And under the sun</i>

03:09.231 --> 03:12.861
<i>This is your world my darling</i>

03:12.943 --> 03:16.618
<i>One world, the land and sea</i>

03:16.697 --> 03:20.998
<i>My hope for you for always</i>

03:21.118 --> 03:26.466
<i>Is that your heart will hold part of me</i>

03:39.511 --> 03:41.184
<i>Down to the sea we go</i>

03:41.263 --> 03:44.858
<i>- Up from the sea
- Down to the world below</i>

03:44.933 --> 03:47.186
ALL: <i>Together we come forever to be</i>

03:47.269 --> 03:51.194
<i>Under one sun</i>

03:51.273 --> 03:55.198
<i>The land and the sea</i>

03:56.319 --> 03:58.538
- MAN 1: Congratulations!
- (WHISTLING AND CHEERING)

04:00.490 --> 04:01.457
MAN 2: Wonderful!

04:01.533 --> 04:02.580
(COOING)

04:02.659 --> 04:04.411
My precious Melody,

04:04.494 --> 04:06.337
I'm giving you this locket

04:06.413 --> 04:09.713
so that you will never forget
that part of your heart

04:09.791 --> 04:12.214
will always belong to the sea.

04:14.713 --> 04:16.055
(MUSIC BOX PLAYING)

04:17.382 --> 04:19.009
(COOING CONTINUES)

04:34.608 --> 04:36.030
Melody!

04:37.360 --> 04:38.703
(CACKLING)

04:39.029 --> 04:40.281
A party!

04:41.323 --> 04:42.791
Ursula's crazy sister!

04:42.866 --> 04:46.916
I didn't miss the cake and ice cream,
did I? (LAUGHING)

04:46.995 --> 04:48.918
Morgana!

04:50.665 --> 04:52.417
Surrender the baby, or I'll...

04:52.501 --> 04:53.844
Ah-ah-ah.

04:55.962 --> 04:58.636
Ursula would have simply
loved to have come,

04:58.715 --> 05:00.717
but something came up.

05:00.801 --> 05:04.897
Now, what was it? Oh, yes.

05:04.971 --> 05:07.474
- (GASPS)
- You all shish-kebabbed her!

05:07.557 --> 05:11.107
One minute you're on top,
the next you're sushi.

05:11.895 --> 05:14.774
Now, is that fair, Gramps? I ask you.

05:14.856 --> 05:18.110
But then, whoever said
we had to play fair?

05:18.235 --> 05:19.737
(CACKLES)

05:19.945 --> 05:22.414
Oh, Undertow!

05:24.241 --> 05:26.494
Make way, little mershrimp!

05:26.576 --> 05:28.749
I'm comin' through!

05:32.415 --> 05:33.587
(GASPS)

05:33.875 --> 05:35.092
(MELODY COOING)

05:35.919 --> 05:37.512
Hand over the trident,

05:37.587 --> 05:41.308
or your precious granddaughter
will be shark chow!

05:41.383 --> 05:44.432
You can have anything you want.

05:44.511 --> 05:46.934
Just don't harm little Melody.

05:47.430 --> 05:48.773
Well, well.

05:49.099 --> 05:51.022
I get the trident,

05:51.101 --> 05:55.197
avenge poor, unfortunate Ursula,

05:55.272 --> 05:58.196
and gain all the powers of the ocean,

05:58.275 --> 06:00.778
and it's not even 10:00.

06:01.278 --> 06:02.780
Not a bad morning.

06:07.701 --> 06:09.294
- Hit the deck!
- (GROANS)

06:10.287 --> 06:11.880
Ahh! Ohh!

06:12.789 --> 06:13.836
(BOTH SCREAM)

06:14.040 --> 06:15.132
(COOING CONTINUES)

06:21.172 --> 06:22.264
(GASPS)

06:23.967 --> 06:25.184
Melody!

06:26.761 --> 06:28.980
What have you done to me? Look at me!

06:29.055 --> 06:30.898
I'm an anchovy! Ah!

06:31.057 --> 06:33.651
This isn't the end, Triton!
It's just the beginning!

06:34.019 --> 06:35.441
After her!

06:35.645 --> 06:36.737
(MORGANA CACKLING)

06:40.525 --> 06:42.448
You'll never find me!

06:42.527 --> 06:44.325
But I'll find you

06:44.404 --> 06:48.079
and your precious granddaughter!

06:48.158 --> 06:52.379
We shall not rest
until that madwoman is vanquished!

06:52.454 --> 06:56.175
Find her!

07:06.468 --> 07:10.974
TRITON: I'm sorry.
There is no sign of her. She's vanished.

07:12.307 --> 07:14.730
- We'll keep trying.
- ARIEL: Sweetie, no.

07:15.727 --> 07:19.106
Oh, we've got to keep Melody
away from her.

07:19.189 --> 07:22.659
Until Morgana is found,
Melody can't go in the sea.

07:24.277 --> 07:25.449
And neither will I.

07:25.528 --> 07:28.577
- But, Ariel...
- I'm sorry, Flounder.

07:28.657 --> 07:33.458
But if Morgana is anything like Ursula,
she'll never give up.

07:33.870 --> 07:35.793
This is the only way.

07:35.872 --> 07:39.297
Melody can't know about
merpeople or Atlantica

07:40.168 --> 07:42.421
or even you, Daddy.

07:42.504 --> 07:43.721
(SIGHS)

07:43.797 --> 07:45.299
Very well, Ariel.

07:45.382 --> 07:46.804
You're right.

07:49.844 --> 07:52.768
Sebastian, you will watch over her.

07:52.847 --> 07:54.019
Me?

07:54.265 --> 07:55.517
Aww!

09:11.843 --> 09:13.766
ARIEL: Melody?

09:13.845 --> 09:15.392
(PEOPLE CHATTERING)

09:17.307 --> 09:18.559
Melody?

09:18.641 --> 09:21.565
Oh, Carlotta, have you seen Melody?

09:21.644 --> 09:24.739
Not since this morning, Your Majesty.

09:24.939 --> 09:25.986
(CHEF LOUIS HUMMING)

09:26.066 --> 09:28.615
Louis, Melody's not in here, is she?

09:29.069 --> 09:32.448
No, Your Highness,
but her birthday cake is.

09:32.530 --> 09:34.453
Twelve petite candles.

09:34.532 --> 09:36.500
<i>C'est magnifique!</i>

09:36.951 --> 09:38.203
Whoa-ohh!

09:38.953 --> 09:40.205
(CHUCKLES)

09:43.583 --> 09:44.709
Whoo-eee!

09:44.793 --> 09:47.888
This is gonna be some kind of shindig.

09:48.004 --> 09:52.134
Yes, sir,
a real swanky soiree, as they say.

09:52.217 --> 09:56.017
There's just one thing missing,
the guest of honour!

10:01.267 --> 10:03.986
"Sebastian, you watch over her,"
he said.

10:05.688 --> 10:06.689
(GRUNTS)

10:06.773 --> 10:08.571
I'm too old for this!

10:08.650 --> 10:11.870
A crab my age
should be retired, getting a tan,

10:12.612 --> 10:14.285
playing sea golf,

10:14.364 --> 10:16.412
sipping a tuna colada!

10:17.325 --> 10:20.044
Not baby-sitting another teenager.

10:24.207 --> 10:25.584
Oh. Hmm.

10:36.719 --> 10:37.720
(GASPS) Melody!

10:51.776 --> 10:52.823
(SIGHS)

10:52.902 --> 10:55.325
Hey, Scuttle.
Hey, Sebastian. What's kickin'?

10:55.905 --> 10:59.000
Uh, hat's kickin'? Hmm. Let me see.

11:00.076 --> 11:01.077
Don't rush me.

11:01.244 --> 11:04.214
Ha! You know perfectly well
what's kicking.

11:04.289 --> 11:06.792
Now, come along.
You gonna be late for the...

11:06.875 --> 11:08.377
- (SPLASHING)
- (COUGHING)

11:10.837 --> 11:12.180
(GIGGLING)

11:12.255 --> 11:14.053
Sorry, Sebastian.

11:14.215 --> 11:18.345
Melody, child,
how many times do I have to tell you?

11:18.428 --> 11:21.307
BOTH: It is expressly forbidden
for you to be swimming

11:21.431 --> 11:22.978
beyond the safety of the sea wall.

11:23.057 --> 11:24.400
Beyond the safety of the sea wall.

11:24.475 --> 11:27.149
Any such swimming
is a reckless disregard of the rules,

11:27.228 --> 11:29.322
don't you know?

11:30.064 --> 11:31.737
- Stop that.
- (GIGGLES)

11:32.108 --> 11:34.406
Oh, Sebastian, I can't help it.

11:34.485 --> 11:36.112
I just love the sea!

11:36.196 --> 11:39.621
Hey! (COUGHING) Come back here!

11:40.950 --> 11:43.123
You're just like,

11:43.244 --> 11:45.167
like your mother.

11:52.337 --> 11:54.760
(CHORTLING) Hi, Melody.

12:35.046 --> 12:36.844
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

12:38.883 --> 12:40.055
(MORGANA LAUGHING)

12:40.134 --> 12:41.431
Trust me!

12:41.511 --> 12:44.185
This time I'm sure I've got it right.

12:44.305 --> 12:47.900
Yeah, that's what you said last time,
and I was sore for a week.

12:47.976 --> 12:50.274
Oh, stop your carping and stand still.

12:50.353 --> 12:52.697
Oh, this is gonna hurt.

13:00.238 --> 13:04.209
Yes. Yes. Yes!

13:04.701 --> 13:05.702
Uh-oh.

13:08.288 --> 13:09.335
(SIGHS)

13:11.291 --> 13:12.338
Hmph!

13:18.089 --> 13:19.090
Aw!

13:25.722 --> 13:26.974
(GROANS)

13:27.223 --> 13:28.395
(SNICKERING)

13:28.641 --> 13:29.642
Oh.

13:29.726 --> 13:31.649
It's just no use.

13:31.728 --> 13:36.359
The power of the trident
is just too strong for me to overcome.

13:37.025 --> 13:38.618
I bet Ursula could've done it.

13:38.693 --> 13:42.448
What was that you said?

13:42.697 --> 13:44.950
Nothin'. I'm just sayin'...

13:47.285 --> 13:49.538
Stop criticising me!

13:49.620 --> 13:52.749
That's all my mother ever did
was criticise me.

13:53.082 --> 13:57.428
It was always Ursula this or Ursula that

13:57.503 --> 14:01.599
or, "Morgana, why can't you be
more like your sister

14:01.716 --> 14:04.014
"Ursula!"

14:04.093 --> 14:06.846
Well, it isn't
Ursula's fault I got miniaturised.

14:06.929 --> 14:08.397
- It's yours!
- Is not!

14:08.473 --> 14:12.899
Your fault that we had to hide out here
for 12 frostbitten years.

14:12.977 --> 14:14.979
- Is not!
- Your fault that we can never

14:15.104 --> 14:17.857
show our faces in polite society again!

14:18.358 --> 14:22.033
You're really pushing it, small fry.

14:32.288 --> 14:33.335
(MORGANA GASPS)

14:33.414 --> 14:35.291
BOTH: It's the locket!

14:35.416 --> 14:36.838
Ooh-ha-ha!

14:37.210 --> 14:40.805
This is just the kind of break
in the ice we've been waiting for.

14:41.089 --> 14:43.592
When Ariel's innocent little daughter

14:43.674 --> 14:46.393
uncovers the secret of that locket,

14:46.469 --> 14:48.767
she's going to have lots of questions.

14:49.389 --> 14:52.984
And who'll be right there
with all the answers?

14:53.101 --> 14:55.195
- (CHUCKLES) We will.
- Exactly!

14:55.311 --> 14:58.941
She'll be the perfect tool
for Triton's undoing.

14:59.023 --> 15:00.946
And I'll get to be big again.

15:01.025 --> 15:05.246
Finally I'll succeed
at the one thing my sister never could.

15:05.363 --> 15:07.661
Really, really big again!

15:07.740 --> 15:10.084
Total domination of the seas!

15:10.159 --> 15:12.457
- (CACKLING)
- (LAUGHING) I'll be huge!

15:15.498 --> 15:17.171
Melody, please.

15:17.250 --> 15:20.424
If your mother ever found out
you'd been swimming out here...

15:20.503 --> 15:23.473
I know, I know. She'd flip.

15:25.383 --> 15:27.306
I had a thought here.

15:27.385 --> 15:30.685
Now, where'd it go? Hmm.

15:32.807 --> 15:37.278
Hey, Sebastian, what's my mom
got against the ocean anyway?

15:39.355 --> 15:43.405
I mean, how could there
be anything wrong with something so

15:44.527 --> 15:46.655
wonderful?

15:47.113 --> 15:48.535
(MELODY GIGGLES)

15:49.365 --> 15:50.617
You know what?

15:50.700 --> 15:52.794
Sometimes I even pretend

15:52.869 --> 15:54.837
I have fins.

15:58.583 --> 15:59.630
(SIGHS)

15:59.709 --> 16:03.088
I wish I could tell my mom how I feel.

16:03.421 --> 16:06.641
But she'd never understand.

16:06.716 --> 16:09.060
I can talk to crabs, but

16:09.677 --> 16:10.894
not to her.

16:15.558 --> 16:17.481
Wait a minute. (GROANS)

16:17.560 --> 16:19.153
It just hit me.

16:19.562 --> 16:21.735
How 'bout you tell Ariel

16:21.814 --> 16:24.363
how you really feel?

16:24.442 --> 16:26.820
Oh, yes, by all means.

16:26.903 --> 16:29.873
Just waltz right in
and tell her you been out here

16:29.947 --> 16:31.949
swimming in the ocean!

16:32.033 --> 16:33.626
We could all just have a big party.

16:33.743 --> 16:35.336
(GASPS) The party!

16:35.620 --> 16:38.419
Say, that reminds me of somethin'.

17:05.608 --> 17:06.951
(MAX BARKING)

17:36.973 --> 17:38.896
- Whoa!
- Oh, Your... Your Highness.

17:38.975 --> 17:41.023
Sorry. My fault.

17:41.143 --> 17:44.317
I gotta go.
Can't go to the party without shoes.

17:44.397 --> 17:45.489
(GIGGLES)

17:45.815 --> 17:49.285
If you ask me, she's a little strange.

17:49.360 --> 17:53.081
- I heard she actually talks to fish.
- (ALL LAUGHING)

17:53.948 --> 17:55.325
BOY 1: You're kidding.

17:55.408 --> 17:57.661
BOY 2: It should make
for an interesting party.

17:57.743 --> 18:00.166
GIRL: Yes! I should say! (LAUGHING)

18:00.538 --> 18:01.710
(MAX BARKING)

18:07.753 --> 18:09.050
(SNIFFING)

18:09.297 --> 18:10.298
(PANTING)

18:11.507 --> 18:13.225
- (SEAGULLS CALLING)
- (SIGHS)

18:14.427 --> 18:16.054
I miss you, Daddy.

18:16.137 --> 18:18.936
I wish you could be here with us.

18:23.185 --> 18:24.528
(SIGHS)

18:30.192 --> 18:31.910
(SIGHS)

18:33.112 --> 18:34.614
- Mother?
- (GASPS)

18:34.697 --> 18:37.200
- What are you doing?
- Uh, nothing.

18:38.951 --> 18:39.952
(BOTH SIGH)

18:40.036 --> 18:41.754
ARIEL: I'll be right up!

18:55.885 --> 18:57.887
Melody?

18:58.137 --> 18:59.138
(GASPS)

19:00.806 --> 19:01.807
(SPUTTERS)

19:09.231 --> 19:11.154
I'm ready.

19:13.235 --> 19:14.407
(CHUCKLES)

19:14.654 --> 19:16.873
Here. Let me help.

19:18.366 --> 19:19.367
(DOOR OPENS)

19:19.450 --> 19:21.919
So, we're having a bad hair day.

19:21.994 --> 19:25.248
If we were,
you wouldn't be helping, would you?

19:25.331 --> 19:28.175
I'm just here to let you know there are
a lot of people downstairs...

19:28.250 --> 19:31.003
Oh, we'll be right down.
Give us two minutes.

19:31.087 --> 19:34.307
(CHUCKLING) Right, two...
Where have I heard that before?

19:40.721 --> 19:42.519
Mom, put down the brush.

19:42.598 --> 19:44.521
- It's hopeless.
- Oh.

19:45.810 --> 19:48.233
You look beautiful.

19:48.771 --> 19:50.819
Do I have to do this?

19:50.898 --> 19:53.447
Everybody thinks I'm weird.

19:53.776 --> 19:58.031
Oh, honey, everyone has trouble
fitting in at your age.

19:58.114 --> 20:00.082
I know I did.

20:00.157 --> 20:02.535
I was a regular fish out of water.

20:02.660 --> 20:04.958
You? No way.

20:06.914 --> 20:10.214
I'm just so afraid
I'm gonna make a total fool of myself.

20:11.460 --> 20:14.714
Melody, this isn't just
about the party, is it?

20:16.132 --> 20:18.635
Is there something
you want to talk about?

20:18.801 --> 20:21.725
You know you can always
tell me anything.

20:24.265 --> 20:26.438
Well, okay.

20:26.517 --> 20:29.487
I mean, it's kinda crazy and

20:29.562 --> 20:31.405
sort of impossible.

20:31.480 --> 20:33.107
Now, don't freak,

20:33.190 --> 20:36.114
but what I dream about
more than anything in the whole world...

20:36.193 --> 20:38.287
- (TAPPING ON GLASS)
- How's it coming?

20:38.362 --> 20:40.740
Oh, Melody. Is that you?

20:40.823 --> 20:42.245
You look beautiful.

20:42.742 --> 20:43.914
(GIGGLES)

20:43.993 --> 20:46.291
He's right. Now, we'll talk later.

20:46.370 --> 20:50.500
You're going to have
a wonderful time tonight. Trust me.

21:00.009 --> 21:03.183
May I present Her Royal Highness,

21:03.679 --> 21:06.102
Princess Melody.

21:07.683 --> 21:11.404
Oh, yeah. Mom's right. I can do this.

21:11.896 --> 21:13.569
(MUFFLED SHOUTS)

21:21.864 --> 21:25.869
Um, hi. Would you like to dance?

21:28.621 --> 21:29.622
(WHISPERS) Go on.

21:31.040 --> 21:32.963
Sure. Okay.

21:35.461 --> 21:37.179
(MUFFLED SHOUTS CONTINUE)

21:48.724 --> 21:50.271
(WALTZ MUSIC PLAYING)

22:08.577 --> 22:10.079
(GROANS)

22:14.250 --> 22:15.843
(MUFFLED SHOUTS CONTINUE)

22:17.002 --> 22:18.003
(GASPS)

22:21.048 --> 22:22.049
- (CRUNCH)
- Yeow!

22:23.300 --> 22:24.472
(GASPS)

22:24.593 --> 22:25.719
(YELLING)

22:26.470 --> 22:27.471
Huh?

22:27.721 --> 22:29.189
(YELLING CONTINUES)

22:29.515 --> 22:30.516
Ahh!

22:35.396 --> 22:36.773
(HUMMING)

22:38.983 --> 22:40.075
(LOUD SPLAT)

22:40.150 --> 22:41.276
- Hmm
- (LAUGHS)

22:41.694 --> 22:43.196
(GUESTS MURMURING)

22:45.406 --> 22:47.329
- Oh, no!
- That's it.

22:47.408 --> 22:49.831
I'm booking myself on a cruise.

22:50.661 --> 22:53.631
- I'm so sorry.
- Well, I should say!

22:53.789 --> 22:56.258
- Are you okay, Sebastian?
- So.

22:56.458 --> 22:59.132
- Who is she talking to?
- (LAUGHING)

22:59.295 --> 23:01.969
- She's talking to a crab!
- (GUESTS LAUGHING)

23:03.549 --> 23:04.550
(GASPS)

23:04.633 --> 23:05.634
You!

23:06.260 --> 23:07.261
(GASPS)

23:07.803 --> 23:09.180
- (SHRIEKS)
- Saboteur!

23:10.139 --> 23:11.607
(LAUGHING CONTINUES)

23:13.058 --> 23:15.561
You're going in the bouillabaisse!

23:16.145 --> 23:18.864
Oh, no! No, Louis!
You don't wanna do this, man!

23:19.106 --> 23:20.699
I'm old! I'm not tender any more!

23:23.277 --> 23:24.403
Louis!

23:24.486 --> 23:25.487
(GROWLS)

23:27.990 --> 23:29.037
Ah!

23:29.116 --> 23:30.117
Huh?

23:43.255 --> 23:44.757
Melody!

23:44.840 --> 23:45.841
(GROWLS)

23:45.925 --> 23:48.769
Death to the crab!

23:49.470 --> 23:50.596
(SPUTTERS)

23:50.679 --> 23:52.602
Oh, Louis!

23:59.939 --> 24:01.407
(SOBBING)

24:12.493 --> 24:14.040
(SOBBING CONTINUES)

24:14.912 --> 24:16.129
(DOOR OPENS)

24:16.747 --> 24:17.919
(DOOR CLOSES)

24:19.541 --> 24:21.543
Oh, sweetheart,

24:21.627 --> 24:23.550
I'm so sorry.

24:24.463 --> 24:25.635
What's wrong with me?

24:27.049 --> 24:29.097
Oh, nothing's wrong with you.

24:29.218 --> 24:32.267
Mom, I'm the princess of disaster.

24:35.140 --> 24:37.643
Being a teenager is hard,

24:37.726 --> 24:43.483
and, uh, all kids your age feel awkward.

24:43.565 --> 24:45.943
- And...
- Melody?

24:46.235 --> 24:48.909
What is this? My name's on here.

24:49.321 --> 24:50.322
(GASPS)

24:51.198 --> 24:54.418
- (MUSIC BOX PLAYING)
- That song. Where have I heard it?

24:56.203 --> 24:59.924
It's Atlantica.
With merpeople and everything.

25:00.749 --> 25:03.923
Mother, you always said it
was just an old fish tale.

25:04.586 --> 25:05.883
Where did you get this?

25:06.547 --> 25:09.175
I, I found it.

25:09.258 --> 25:11.727
You went over the wall, didn't you?

25:11.844 --> 25:15.439
Actually, I went under it.
I hate that stupid wall.

25:15.556 --> 25:17.433
Melody, you know you're
not allowed in the sea.

25:17.516 --> 25:19.189
But why?

25:19.268 --> 25:21.191
And why does that necklace
have my name on it?

25:21.270 --> 25:22.863
Melody, listen to me.

25:23.063 --> 25:24.531
You're hiding something from me.

25:25.983 --> 25:27.826
You deliberately disobeyed me!

25:27.943 --> 25:31.493
I never want you going out there again!
It's dangerous in the sea!

25:31.572 --> 25:35.042
How would you know?
You've never even been in it!

25:35.617 --> 25:37.085
(RESUMES SOBBING)

25:37.161 --> 25:38.538
Melody, I...

25:38.620 --> 25:39.712
Uh...

25:40.622 --> 25:42.090
(SIGHS) Oh, no.

25:42.916 --> 25:46.841
Ariel, darling,
we knew this day would come.

25:47.212 --> 25:49.135
Oh, Eric.

25:49.214 --> 25:52.969
You're right.
It's time I trusted her with the truth.

25:55.137 --> 25:58.607
Oh, now, child, it's gonna be okay.

25:59.349 --> 26:01.647
You know, when I was a teenager

26:01.769 --> 26:04.648
you couldn't get me
out of my shell for nothin'.

26:04.730 --> 26:07.074
I had this high, squeaky voice

26:07.149 --> 26:09.277
and these itty-bitty little pincers.

26:09.443 --> 26:11.537
And then one day, boom!

26:11.612 --> 26:16.288
I sound like Caruso
and these whoppers pop out!

26:18.619 --> 26:20.838
Young lady, just where
do you think you're going?

26:21.330 --> 26:22.582
I've gotta figure this out.

26:23.665 --> 26:24.666
(WHIMPERS)

26:24.750 --> 26:26.969
This necklace means something,

26:27.461 --> 26:28.883
and if no one's gonna tell me,

26:30.214 --> 26:32.558
I'm gonna find out myself.

26:32.633 --> 26:33.725
Ahh!

26:34.426 --> 26:35.552
(GASPING)

26:35.636 --> 26:39.061
Melody, please!
You're making a big mistake!

26:39.139 --> 26:40.265
(CHUCKLES)

26:40.349 --> 26:43.398
Oh, this is delicious.

26:43.477 --> 26:45.855
This is divine!

26:45.938 --> 26:48.862
- Let's go, flatsos.
- (MORGANA CHUCKLES)

26:48.941 --> 26:50.488
Hurry, Undertow.

26:50.567 --> 26:54.538
There's a little girl out there
who needs our help.

26:56.115 --> 26:59.870
All right, Sebastian,
you must remain calm.

26:59.993 --> 27:01.415
This is not your fault.

27:01.870 --> 27:05.249
All you have to do
is go in there and calmly explain

27:05.332 --> 27:07.755
that Melody has run away.

27:07.835 --> 27:09.587
No reason to lose your head.

27:09.920 --> 27:13.845
Whatever you do,
you "absitively, " "positutely"

27:13.924 --> 27:16.677
must not panic.

27:16.760 --> 27:17.932
- Melody!
- (GASPS)

27:18.011 --> 27:21.436
- Melody's gone, Melody's gone!
- Sebastian? What are you doing here?

27:21.515 --> 27:24.189
All my fault! I tried to stop her!

27:24.268 --> 27:26.817
(SOBBING) I don't deserve to live!

27:26.895 --> 27:28.693
Gone? Gone where?

27:29.565 --> 27:31.317
Out, out.

27:31.775 --> 27:33.743
To the sea.

27:35.946 --> 27:37.243
(BLOWS NOSE)

27:38.824 --> 27:41.452
What do you mean?
Where could she be going?

27:41.827 --> 27:43.545
To Morgana's.

27:44.079 --> 27:46.502
And she can tell me what this
locket means,

27:46.582 --> 27:48.129
why it has my name on it?

27:48.208 --> 27:50.256
(CHUCKLING) Oh, sure, kid.

27:50.335 --> 27:53.760
Morgana's the best. She'll help ya.

27:55.674 --> 27:58.644
Okay. Then let's go.

28:01.305 --> 28:02.978
(CHUCKLES WICKEDLY)

28:03.724 --> 28:04.816
(SNICKERING)

28:49.394 --> 28:52.523
Angel face, meet the one and only

28:52.606 --> 28:55.109
Morgana.

28:55.192 --> 28:58.742
Oh, welcome, my precious.

28:58.820 --> 29:00.367
Oh, don't be shy.

29:00.989 --> 29:04.289
Come in. Come in out of the cold.

29:05.661 --> 29:07.629
Sit, sit.

29:07.955 --> 29:11.209
Put your feet up.

29:11.291 --> 29:16.013
Hungry? Afraid all I have is a cold plate.
(CHUCKLES)

29:16.630 --> 29:19.554
Smelt-cicle? Kelp chip?

29:19.633 --> 29:21.852
Hush guppy?

29:21.927 --> 29:23.270
Uh, no, thank you.

29:24.179 --> 29:27.228
I was hoping you could
tell me about this pendant,

29:27.307 --> 29:29.605
why it has my name on it.

29:29.726 --> 29:33.196
My mother wouldn't tell me. (SIGHS)

29:33.313 --> 29:35.407
She just doesn't understand.

29:35.482 --> 29:40.283
Oh, you're not the only one with
a mother who doesn't understand you.

29:40.362 --> 29:44.333
Believe me, I know just how you feel.

29:44.825 --> 29:49.956
Dear child, did you ever consider
that it has your name on it

29:50.205 --> 29:53.254
because it has your destiny in it?

29:54.042 --> 29:55.134
(MUSIC BOX PLAYING)

29:55.210 --> 29:58.259
Oh, deep down you know
you weren't meant to be

29:58.338 --> 30:00.636
a lowly human.

30:01.174 --> 30:06.305
What you are is something
far more enchanting.

30:06.388 --> 30:08.231
A mermaid?

30:08.307 --> 30:09.809
But it's not possible.

30:09.891 --> 30:13.020
(CHUCKLES) Darling,
anything's possible.

30:13.103 --> 30:15.697
You can turn me into a mermaid?

30:15.772 --> 30:17.194
Piece of fish cake, honey.

30:17.399 --> 30:18.446
(MUTTERS) Huh!

30:18.525 --> 30:19.617
Lotsa luck.

30:20.110 --> 30:21.532
(HUMMING)

30:23.280 --> 30:24.372
Ah.

30:27.451 --> 30:30.330
Ursula's magic? Where'd you get that?

30:30.412 --> 30:34.167
I've been saving it
for a special occasion.

30:34.249 --> 30:37.503
(CHUCKLES) One drop of this
and, bada-bing, bada-boom!

30:37.586 --> 30:39.964
You're in fin city! Whee!

30:40.213 --> 30:43.057
- Really?
- Come, my darling.

30:43.175 --> 30:46.930
Your destiny awaits you.

30:51.892 --> 30:53.360
(CACKLING)

31:00.942 --> 31:02.364
(CONTINUES CACKLING)

31:06.239 --> 31:08.583
I don't believe it!

31:08.658 --> 31:10.160
I'm a mermaid.

31:10.243 --> 31:12.621
Say it loud, say it proud! (CACKLING)

31:15.123 --> 31:16.466
(LAUGHING)

31:19.878 --> 31:21.972
I'm a mermaid!

31:22.089 --> 31:23.636
(CONTINUES LAUGHING)

31:24.925 --> 31:26.848
You had this all along.

31:26.927 --> 31:29.851
You could've changed me back.
Why, I oughta...

31:29.930 --> 31:32.479
Keep your scales on, small fry.

31:32.557 --> 31:34.730
I'm still reeling her in.

31:38.063 --> 31:40.316
ARIEL: Oh, Daddy, I'm so worried.

31:40.440 --> 31:43.114
Everything's going to be all right, Ariel.

31:43.193 --> 31:45.946
We have search parties
scouring the ocean.

31:46.405 --> 31:48.248
I'm going to join them now myself.

31:48.323 --> 31:51.793
Ariel, maybe you should go with him.

31:52.160 --> 31:53.252
But, Eric...

31:53.328 --> 31:56.002
I need to stay here
and lead the search on land.

31:56.081 --> 31:58.425
But you know these waters,

31:58.500 --> 32:00.673
and you know our daughter.

32:01.002 --> 32:02.549
You have to go.

32:02.629 --> 32:04.131
It may be dangerous.

32:05.924 --> 32:07.392
Eric's right, Daddy.

32:07.467 --> 32:09.970
I should've known
I couldn't keep Melody from the sea.

32:10.053 --> 32:11.600
It's a part of her.

32:12.055 --> 32:13.648
And a part of me.

32:13.765 --> 32:15.062
I have to go.

32:20.689 --> 32:22.191
Bring her home.

32:51.011 --> 32:53.434
What a totally cool feeling!

32:53.722 --> 32:54.939
(GIGGLING) Whee!

32:58.935 --> 32:59.936
(GASPS)

33:00.145 --> 33:01.397
(WHIMPERS)

33:01.521 --> 33:03.740
Oh, excuse me. I'm so sorry, ma'am.

33:07.027 --> 33:10.076
(SINGING) <i>Okay, get a grip</i>
<i>Get the hang of this flipper</i>

33:10.155 --> 33:13.705
<i>It's like slipping two feet
into one big, huge slipper</i>

33:13.825 --> 33:16.829
<i>This way is left
Which way is right</i>

33:16.912 --> 33:20.416
<i>Oh, now I'll be circling
in circles all night</i>

33:20.499 --> 33:22.922
Oh, so this is forward. No problem.

33:23.084 --> 33:25.587
<i>I can't believe I can do this and more</i>

33:25.754 --> 33:29.008
<i>To swim in the sea
like I walk on the shore</i>

33:29.090 --> 33:32.014
<i>Out of my shell
Not closed up like a clam</i>

33:32.093 --> 33:35.063
<i>Look out, sea
This is me</i>

33:35.180 --> 33:38.525
<i>Here I am</i>

33:38.600 --> 33:41.774
<i>For a moment all of me</i>

33:41.853 --> 33:44.902
<i>Is alive and at home in the sea</i>

33:44.981 --> 33:48.155
<i>I'm swirling and twirling
So graceful and grand</i>

33:48.235 --> 33:51.284
<i>Not stubbing my toes
Getting stuck in the sand</i>

33:51.613 --> 33:54.457
<i>For a moment life is cool</i>

33:54.616 --> 33:57.665
<i>I'm a splash in the world's biggest pool</i>

33:57.786 --> 34:01.006
<i>This is more than my thoughts
ever thought it could be</i>

34:01.122 --> 34:04.092
<i>For a moment
Just a moment</i>

34:04.209 --> 34:05.882
<i>Lucky me</i>

34:05.961 --> 34:07.133
(GIGGLING)

34:07.837 --> 34:10.806
<i>If only for one moment</i>

34:10.924 --> 34:14.518
<i>I had shared with you all I know</i>

34:14.803 --> 34:17.898
<i>The sea wouldn't be a mystery</i>

34:17.973 --> 34:20.476
<i>Oh, why did you have to go</i>

34:20.641 --> 34:22.565
<i>Everything's newer
and brighter and bluer</i>

34:22.643 --> 34:25.397
<i>And truer to life than before</i>

34:25.480 --> 34:28.108
<i>Watch me soar</i>

34:28.233 --> 34:31.407
<i>For a moment I can shine</i>

34:31.570 --> 34:34.449
<i>Got a grin and a fin that works fine</i>

34:34.531 --> 34:37.831
<i>My fingers are wrinkly
and I really don't care</i>

34:38.201 --> 34:41.295
<i>If all of my curls
have curled out of my hair</i>

34:41.371 --> 34:44.123
<i>For a moment I can feel</i>

34:44.206 --> 34:47.085
<i>All the dreams
I've been dreaming are real</i>

34:47.168 --> 34:49.170
<i>Wish my mother could hear it</i>

34:49.254 --> 34:50.927
<i>The sea is my song</i>

34:51.005 --> 34:54.179
<i>For a moment
Just a moment</i>

34:54.301 --> 34:55.768
<i>I belong</i>

34:55.844 --> 34:58.097
<i>I will find you, my darling</i>

34:58.847 --> 35:03.318
<i>And the moment that I do</i>

35:03.393 --> 35:07.148
<i>I'll hold you close, my Melody</i>

35:07.230 --> 35:11.360
<i>And sing the song of the sea</i>

35:11.443 --> 35:14.617
<i>With you</i>

35:14.696 --> 35:18.496
<i>- Sing the song of the sea
- For a moment, just a moment</i>

35:18.575 --> 35:25.379
<i>- With you
- I belong</i>

35:35.133 --> 35:38.262
Oh, thank you! Thank you so much!

35:38.345 --> 35:39.312
Oh. (SNIFFLING)

35:39.387 --> 35:40.388
What's the matter?

35:40.972 --> 35:43.475
Oh, I knew this would happen.

35:43.558 --> 35:45.276
One taste, and you're hooked.

35:45.727 --> 35:49.652
Oh, Undertow,
I'm such a failure, such a...

35:51.399 --> 35:52.946
Oh, my precious,

35:53.026 --> 35:56.701
there wasn't enough potion
for this to be a forever spell.

35:57.572 --> 36:02.078
Please, I don't want
to go back to being an ordinary girl.

36:03.036 --> 36:05.835
Isn't there some way
I can stay a mermaid?

36:05.914 --> 36:10.715
No, I'm afraid there's
absolutely no possible way.

36:10.794 --> 36:12.717
Well, there is one way.

36:12.796 --> 36:16.391
No. What am I thinking?
It's far too dangerous.

36:16.466 --> 36:19.345
What? What's too dangerous?

36:19.594 --> 36:23.895
Well, I could make the spell last longer

36:23.973 --> 36:26.817
if I had my magic trident.

36:26.893 --> 36:32.024
Oh, but it was stolen years ago
by a deranged kleptomaniac,

36:32.107 --> 36:35.702
and there's no one to get it back for me.

36:35.777 --> 36:37.404
Maybe I could get it back for you.

36:38.113 --> 36:40.491
You would do that for me?

36:41.241 --> 36:44.165
If I did, would you
make me a mermaid forever?

36:44.244 --> 36:47.168
Even longer, if you like. (CHUCKLES)

36:47.789 --> 36:51.339
Now, here is where the scoundrel lives.

36:51.543 --> 36:55.264
Atlantica?
You mean it's not just an old fish tale?

36:55.338 --> 36:56.681
It really exists?

36:56.756 --> 36:59.134
Of course it exists, dear.

36:59.217 --> 37:01.265
Whoever told you otherwise?

37:01.344 --> 37:03.267
My mother.

37:03.346 --> 37:08.603
Well, I'm sure she didn't mean
to be cruel and deceitful.

37:08.685 --> 37:11.734
Okay, I'll bring back your trident.

37:11.813 --> 37:13.190
You can count on me!

37:13.273 --> 37:14.991
Be careful, dear.

37:15.108 --> 37:18.203
Enjoy those fins!

37:18.278 --> 37:20.827
While you can.

37:21.197 --> 37:22.870
(CHUCKLES WICKEDLY)

37:29.414 --> 37:31.257
Hmm. Let's see.

37:31.332 --> 37:34.211
South to Two Circles Pass,

37:34.294 --> 37:36.922
then, uh, north to...

37:37.338 --> 37:39.466
No, no, um, east to...

37:40.175 --> 37:41.347
Uh... Hmm.

37:42.510 --> 37:43.682
Ah...

37:44.429 --> 37:45.430
Ah...

37:46.097 --> 37:47.098
Ah...

37:47.182 --> 37:48.434
- (SNEEZES)
- Whoa!

37:49.601 --> 37:50.898
(GROANS)

37:51.311 --> 37:52.312
(SIGHS)

37:53.480 --> 37:56.859
My map. It's ruined.

37:57.025 --> 37:59.619
Now how am I gonna
find my way to Atlantica?

37:59.694 --> 38:02.368
Help! Someone, please!

38:02.489 --> 38:06.369
Help! Oh! Oh, hold on, sweetie!
We'll save you!

38:06.576 --> 38:10.877
Help! Mama! Hurry!

38:10.955 --> 38:12.878
I can't reach her.

38:12.957 --> 38:14.049
- (ALL GRUNTING)
- (ALL MURMURING)

38:14.125 --> 38:15.798
Somebody help us!

38:15.877 --> 38:17.254
(TIP SINGS FANFARE)

38:18.213 --> 38:21.217
Mightier than a hurricane!
Braver than a killer whale!

38:23.718 --> 38:25.391
Faster than a moray eel!

38:25.678 --> 38:27.476
It's the fearless adventurers...

38:27.555 --> 38:29.398
Slash-explorers.

38:29.474 --> 38:33.399
Titanic Tip
and his trusty sidekick Dash!

38:33.812 --> 38:36.190
- Oh, no.
- Not them.

38:36.314 --> 38:37.440
(CHUCKLES)

38:37.524 --> 38:39.947
This is it, Dash. Redemption.

38:40.026 --> 38:41.653
No, not the walrus.

38:41.736 --> 38:44.330
- DASH: Sorry. Excuse me.
- Ow!

38:44.405 --> 38:46.328
Oh, was that your face?

38:46.407 --> 38:48.660
We're finally gonna be heroes for real.

38:48.743 --> 38:52.043
Yeah, they're not gonna
laugh at us any more.

38:52.789 --> 38:54.883
- This is too easy.
- (GRUNTING)

38:54.958 --> 38:59.134
And a-one, and a-two,

38:59.212 --> 39:01.089
and a shark...

39:01.506 --> 39:04.760
- Shark?
- Shark!

39:04.843 --> 39:07.312
DASH: Shark, shark, shark!
TIP: Comin' through!

39:07.804 --> 39:10.432
- Goin' up, goin' up, goin' up!
- Goin' down.

39:10.598 --> 39:11.690
(ALL SCREAM)

39:11.766 --> 39:13.109
(ALL GRUNTING)

39:13.601 --> 39:14.727
Ahh!

39:14.936 --> 39:16.654
Oh! Mmm! Mmm.

39:17.021 --> 39:20.070
- (ALL GRUNTING)
- TIP: Get off me!

39:22.235 --> 39:23.612
(ALL SCREAMING)

39:28.032 --> 39:29.955
Well, that wasn't so bad.

39:32.662 --> 39:34.414
(ALL SCREAMING)

39:45.675 --> 39:46.676
Oh.

39:48.761 --> 39:50.684
- Mama!
- Mmm!

39:53.766 --> 39:56.690
Another plan perfectly executed.

39:56.769 --> 39:58.612
What did you think you were doing?

39:59.647 --> 40:02.526
We were just trying to be heroes.

40:02.609 --> 40:05.362
You call abandoning my baby heroic?

40:05.945 --> 40:07.993
You two boys almost got us all killed.

40:08.114 --> 40:10.867
Oh, yeah, some fearless heroes.

40:10.950 --> 40:13.794
- More like zeroes!
- (ALL LAUGHING)

40:16.706 --> 40:18.083
PENGUIN: That's a good one!

40:18.541 --> 40:22.091
Go ahead.
Laugh your stinkin' tuxedos off.

40:23.087 --> 40:25.510
We'll show you, someday.

40:33.765 --> 40:34.766
- Excuse me.
- Ahh!

40:34.849 --> 40:36.351
Ohh! Ooh!

40:37.018 --> 40:39.862
You don't have to be scared of me.
I won't hurt you.

40:40.355 --> 40:43.234
Scared? Who said anything
about bein' scared?

40:43.316 --> 40:45.990
Don't you know an evasive manoeuvre
when you see one?

40:46.194 --> 40:47.241
(GIGGLES)

40:47.320 --> 40:49.038
Hi. I'm Melody.

40:49.238 --> 40:51.332
This here's Tip, and I'm Dash.

40:51.407 --> 40:54.911
Excuse me, Mr I Spill My Guts
To Total Strangers.

40:55.203 --> 40:58.628
- You just blew our cover.
- I was just trying to be friendly.

40:59.248 --> 41:01.717
Uh, guys, I really need to get going,

41:01.793 --> 41:03.591
so if you could just tell me...

41:03.670 --> 41:07.971
See? Now she's gonna leave,
and it's all your fault.

41:08.049 --> 41:10.051
My fault? (SPUTTERS)

41:10.259 --> 41:13.638
- Guys...
- She's probably allergic to blubber.

41:13.721 --> 41:15.314
Oh, yeah?

41:15.390 --> 41:19.361
Well, maybe she doesn't like
birds that can't fly!

41:19.435 --> 41:21.312
- (GASPS)
- Guys...

41:21.396 --> 41:22.397
Well, you can't fly either.

41:22.480 --> 41:25.029
And you walk funny.

41:25.108 --> 41:27.031
- Guys!
- Oh, yeah?

41:27.110 --> 41:30.364
Well, you can't fly either!

41:30.446 --> 41:32.289
Guys!

41:32.365 --> 41:36.415
Do either of you know how to get
to Atlantica? I don't have much time.

41:36.494 --> 41:37.916
Why do you want to go to Atlantica?

41:38.329 --> 41:41.549
I have to get something
that was stolen from a friend.

41:41.624 --> 41:44.753
If I don't, I'll turn back into...

41:45.044 --> 41:47.547
A what? Turn back into a what?

41:47.630 --> 41:48.631
A human.

41:48.756 --> 41:49.848
(GASPS)

41:50.466 --> 41:52.969
I knew there was something
unfishy about you.

41:53.428 --> 41:55.806
Tough break, sister. Drop us a line.

41:55.888 --> 41:58.061
Let us know how it all turns out.

41:58.141 --> 41:59.643
- We'll take you.
- You will?

41:59.767 --> 42:02.520
- We will?
- She's a damsel in distress.

42:02.603 --> 42:04.697
It's our big chance.

42:10.695 --> 42:12.368
Whew. Hoo-boy.

42:12.447 --> 42:15.496
I can't believe I'm doing this.
Somebody stop me.

42:15.575 --> 42:16.952
All right, then, we're in.

42:17.035 --> 42:19.458
On to Atlantica!

42:23.124 --> 42:24.296
A-ha!

42:24.792 --> 42:26.715
(SINGING) <i>Taming the tides</i>

42:26.794 --> 42:28.796
<i>Swarming the seas</i>

42:28.880 --> 42:31.804
<i>Beware, barracudas
Drop to your knees</i>

42:31.924 --> 42:32.925
Aah!

42:33.009 --> 42:35.853
<i>Defending our friends and anemones</i>

42:35.928 --> 42:36.929
<i>As big as a whale</i>

42:37.013 --> 42:38.014
Hey!

42:38.097 --> 42:39.940
<i>With a much smaller tail</i>

42:40.016 --> 42:43.896
<i>Facing the foe with our fearless flukes</i>

42:43.978 --> 42:47.778
<i>Daring the dastards
to put up their dukes</i>

42:47.857 --> 42:51.077
<i>Great globs of gore
We'll storm the shore</i>

42:51.152 --> 42:53.246
<i>And seek the unknown</i>

42:53.321 --> 42:55.540
Then can we go home?

42:55.615 --> 42:57.538
BOTH: <i>Titanic Tip and Daring Dash</i>

42:57.617 --> 42:59.210
<i>Adventurers-slash-explorers</i>

42:59.285 --> 43:01.037
<i>Titanic Tip and Daring Dash</i>

43:01.120 --> 43:03.122
<i>Adventurers-slash-explorers</i>

43:03.206 --> 43:04.924
<i>Our gallant quest to do our best</i>

43:04.999 --> 43:06.967
<i>And smile for our adorers</i>

43:07.043 --> 43:08.920
MELODY: <i>We'll save the day</i>
DASH: <i>And make a splash</i>

43:09.003 --> 43:11.301
<i>Titanic Tip and Daring Dash</i>

43:14.509 --> 43:17.729
<i>We'll clobber those crabs
with their clammy claws</i>

43:17.804 --> 43:21.024
<i>We'll shatter those sharks
with their savage jaws</i>

43:21.140 --> 43:24.565
<i>- The battle is fierce
- And mercifully brief</i>

43:24.685 --> 43:28.360
<i>The conquering heroes return
as kings of the reef</i>

43:28.689 --> 43:30.817
<i>We'll dine with the best</i>

43:31.067 --> 43:33.161
<i>Dressed with a flair</i>

43:33.236 --> 43:35.159
<i>Climb every mountain</i>

43:35.238 --> 43:36.956
<i>Because it's there</i>

43:37.073 --> 43:41.044
<i>Come on, follow me
We'll make history</i>

43:41.202 --> 43:43.045
<i>To courage
To us</i>

43:43.204 --> 43:44.922
<i>- The trident
- Or bust</i>

43:45.039 --> 43:47.462
ALL: <i>Titanic Tip and Daring Dash</i>

43:47.542 --> 43:49.089
<i>Adventurers-slash-explorers</i>

43:49.168 --> 43:51.136
<i>Titanic Tip and Daring Dash</i>

43:51.212 --> 43:52.759
<i>Adventurers-slash-explorers</i>

43:52.839 --> 43:55.058
<i>- We'll save the day
- And make a splash</i>

43:55.174 --> 43:56.847
<i>- Melody
- Tip and Daring Dash</i>

43:57.009 --> 43:58.761
ALL: <i>All for three and three for one</i>

43:58.845 --> 44:00.939
<i>Atlantica</i>

44:01.013 --> 44:07.988
<i>Here we come</i>

44:09.522 --> 44:12.446
MELODY: I knew it! It's real!

44:12.525 --> 44:14.448
- Atlantica.
- (MORGANA CHUCKLES)

44:14.527 --> 44:16.996
That's right, Princess.

44:17.071 --> 44:19.494
Just a little further.

44:19.574 --> 44:21.292
Cloak! Dagger!

44:21.367 --> 44:26.874
Go make sure that no one interferes
with her return. Hmm?

44:30.334 --> 44:31.802
Have you heard anything, Daddy?

44:31.919 --> 44:35.264
I've been searching everywhere,
but I'd... Flounder!

44:37.758 --> 44:40.011
Daddy!

44:40.219 --> 44:42.142
FLOUNDER: Now what?

44:42.680 --> 44:43.681
(CHUCKLES)

44:43.764 --> 44:45.311
- Sorry.
- Ariel?

44:45.391 --> 44:47.359
- Flounder?
- Ariel!

44:47.435 --> 44:50.860
Oh, I've missed you! (GIGGLES)

44:50.938 --> 44:53.862
Boy, you're sure not a guppy any more.

44:53.941 --> 44:56.569
(CHUCKLES) You can say that again.

44:56.652 --> 44:58.700
- Over here!
- Throw it to me!

44:59.572 --> 45:01.290
- Yeah!
- I want it!

45:01.616 --> 45:02.663
Ow!

45:03.201 --> 45:05.545
Children, what did I say

45:05.620 --> 45:08.373
about playing Kick the Clam
on the reef?

45:08.456 --> 45:10.925
- Sorry, Dad.
- Kids. (CHUCKLES)

45:13.920 --> 45:15.638
I'm sorry about Melody.

45:17.215 --> 45:20.640
Flounder, I really need your help.

45:21.594 --> 45:24.518
Wild sea horses couldn't stop me.

45:29.352 --> 45:31.320
GUPPY 1: Oh, boy!
GUPPY 2: Follow me!

45:32.188 --> 45:34.156
GUPPY 3: Come on!

45:40.905 --> 45:43.875
(SIGHS) It's so beautiful.

45:43.950 --> 45:44.951
BOTH: Whoa!

45:45.034 --> 45:46.411
- Sorry. My...
- Sorry. My fault.

45:46.827 --> 45:48.329
- ...fault.
- Hi.

45:49.664 --> 45:50.665
Uh...

45:50.748 --> 45:53.467
I don't think I've seen you around here.
What's your name?

45:53.834 --> 45:56.758
I'm Mel... Mel...

45:56.837 --> 45:59.135
Hey, guys! Meet Mel-Mel.

45:59.215 --> 46:01.638
- Hi.
- Hey, you wanna hang out with us?

46:02.385 --> 46:04.888
All right, all right.
Break it up. Break it up!

46:05.054 --> 46:07.682
There's nothing to see here.
Move along.

46:07.848 --> 46:09.521
Come on, Miss Popularity.

46:09.892 --> 46:12.190
We have a previous engagement.
Remember?

46:13.521 --> 46:15.194
Maybe I'll catch you later.

46:15.523 --> 46:17.116
(SIGHS) This is what happens

46:17.233 --> 46:19.611
when you bring a country fish
to the big city.

46:21.404 --> 46:23.372
Was that a penguin?

46:34.583 --> 46:35.709
Wow!

46:36.252 --> 46:38.175
DASH: Nice crib.

46:46.095 --> 46:48.189
Come on. Follow me.

46:53.185 --> 46:54.311
(MELODY GASPS)

46:54.395 --> 46:57.319
That must be him.

47:00.026 --> 47:02.449
He looks sad.

47:03.237 --> 47:06.081
- He doesn't look like a thief.
- They never do.

47:09.952 --> 47:11.124
Look! There it is!

47:12.580 --> 47:16.255
A fork? We're risking our tails for a fork?

47:21.589 --> 47:23.591
We haven't time for this.

47:23.674 --> 47:25.893
I want every available
merman searching!

47:26.844 --> 47:31.065
Find her!

47:42.276 --> 47:43.619
- (RATTLING)
- Hmm.

47:47.114 --> 47:50.163
Dash, if this is the end,

47:50.242 --> 47:52.119
I just want you to know, pal,

47:52.203 --> 47:54.456
I'm sorry I said that thing
about the blubber.

47:54.580 --> 47:58.710
- Well, I'm sorry about the fish breath.
- Yeah...

47:58.834 --> 48:01.758
- You didn't say anything about that.
- But I was thinkin' it.

48:01.837 --> 48:03.305
(BOTH WHIMPERING)

48:07.968 --> 48:11.313
King Triton, your daughter has returned.

48:21.941 --> 48:24.569
- Ooh, that was close.
- Whew!

48:29.490 --> 48:33.165
Oh, sure, that's it.
Take your time. Kick back. Relax.

48:33.244 --> 48:35.713
Let's all just linger here and die!

48:36.163 --> 48:38.632
I'm sure she'll turn up soon.

48:39.208 --> 48:40.960
He's coming back!

48:46.507 --> 48:47.599
(MELODY GASPS)

48:48.759 --> 48:50.682
My necklace!

48:55.683 --> 48:58.607
Ah, don't worry, Ariel. We'll find her.

49:01.689 --> 49:03.908
Daddy! The trident!

49:06.152 --> 49:08.075
But that's not possible.

49:08.154 --> 49:11.158
Nobody can remove the trident
from the stand except you, sire.

49:11.740 --> 49:13.663
You or one of your descendants.

49:13.742 --> 49:15.039
Melody.

49:15.119 --> 49:17.918
Who I was supposed to be watching.

49:17.997 --> 49:22.548
Go ahead, crack me open.
Make a crab cake out of me, sire.

49:22.710 --> 49:24.804
But how could she have gotten here?

49:24.879 --> 49:29.726
Morgana.
If she gets her hands on my trident...

49:29.800 --> 49:31.473
Double the search parties!

49:31.552 --> 49:33.930
I want every creature
in the ocean on patrol!

49:34.054 --> 49:35.897
Yes, sire!

49:44.690 --> 49:45.737
ARIEL: Wait a minute.

49:46.692 --> 49:48.615
I know those two.

49:49.737 --> 49:51.660
It's all my fault.

49:51.739 --> 49:54.333
If I had just paid a little more attention

49:54.408 --> 49:57.753
instead of blabbering
on and on and on...

50:06.003 --> 50:08.347
...and on and on.

50:08.422 --> 50:12.598
From now on, Your Majesty,
nothing gets past

50:14.261 --> 50:15.262
me.

50:15.429 --> 50:16.476
Whoo-hoo!

50:16.555 --> 50:17.898
Yeah!

50:20.976 --> 50:22.319
We did it!

50:22.394 --> 50:23.941
Uh-huh. Uh...

50:24.021 --> 50:25.022
Hmm?

50:30.402 --> 50:34.623
All this time Atlantica was never
that far away from home.

50:35.074 --> 50:38.123
This is your home?

50:39.286 --> 50:40.412
It used to be.

50:40.621 --> 50:43.750
Whoa, what a pad.
Talk about your kerb appeal.

50:43.832 --> 50:45.129
But what's with the wall?

50:45.459 --> 50:48.258
I know good fences make good
neighbours, but isn't that a bit much?

50:48.337 --> 50:50.180
What you tryin' to keep out?

50:50.256 --> 50:52.384
It wasn't built to keep something out.

50:53.300 --> 50:55.223
It was built to keep me in.

50:55.594 --> 50:58.268
Come on. Let's go.

51:00.808 --> 51:02.731
DASH: Whoa-ho-ho!
TIP: Whoo-hoo!

51:08.107 --> 51:11.361
TIP: You know, kid, the three of us,
we make a pretty good team.

51:11.443 --> 51:15.164
DASH: Once you're a permanent
mermaid, we'll be friends forever.

51:15.239 --> 51:20.245
- We'll be inseparable.
- Nothing will ever come between us.

51:20.327 --> 51:22.750
- Shark! Run! Run!
- Shark!

51:23.622 --> 51:25.044
No, wait!

51:25.332 --> 51:27.926
- It's just...
- (LAUGHS)

51:28.002 --> 51:30.004
Leavin' so soon, boys?

51:30.087 --> 51:32.761
What can I say?
When you got it, you got it.

51:32.840 --> 51:35.343
Hey! You got it!

51:35.426 --> 51:38.179
Sweetheart, you're my new hero.

51:38.262 --> 51:41.983
Let's go. It's time for some magic.

51:42.057 --> 51:44.526
But... But my friends...

51:44.602 --> 51:48.152
Ha! You mean you call those two
yellow-bellied sea slugs your friends?

51:49.023 --> 51:50.115
Come on!

51:50.190 --> 51:52.534
You wanna be a mermaid, or what?

51:52.610 --> 51:55.284
We got the power. We got the power.
(GRUNTING)

51:56.238 --> 51:57.660
We got the power!

52:09.960 --> 52:12.884
(GASPS) So there it is.

52:13.047 --> 52:16.768
Swim back as fast as you can and tell
my father. I'll try to find Melody.

52:16.842 --> 52:21.894
Oh, but if that old sea witch is in there,
and then there's that mean little shark,

52:21.972 --> 52:25.943
and then those manta rays come, and
then she takes those creepy tentacles

52:26.018 --> 52:28.942
so suction cups stick to your face, and...

52:29.063 --> 52:30.565
(SIGHS) Uh-uh.

52:30.648 --> 52:32.946
No way you're going in there alone.

52:33.442 --> 52:34.989
But, Flounder, if we both go,

52:35.069 --> 52:37.788
who's going to tell Daddy
where Morgana's lair is?

52:37.863 --> 52:41.242
What's all the whispering about?
Is Melody around here?

52:41.742 --> 52:44.165
- Did you find her yet? If she's...
- Scuttle!

52:44.244 --> 52:46.212
(WHISPERS) Get down and be quiet.

52:46.872 --> 52:48.419
Wait a minute.

52:48.499 --> 52:50.092
Scuttle can get help.

52:51.669 --> 52:56.345
Scuttle, I need you
to pay very close attention.

52:56.757 --> 52:59.226
We're doomed.

52:59.551 --> 53:01.849
Oh, there you are, darling!

53:01.929 --> 53:04.853
Oh, I was so worried about you.

53:04.932 --> 53:08.778
And look!
You've brought back my trident.

53:08.852 --> 53:12.072
- Clever girl.
- Give it to her! Give it to her!

53:12.940 --> 53:14.032
Hey!

53:14.108 --> 53:17.408
Forgive him, dear.
He's got a little size issue.

53:17.486 --> 53:20.831
Now, if you'll just hand over the...

53:20.906 --> 53:23.625
- Melody, don't! Don't listen to her!
- Mom!

53:26.453 --> 53:28.126
BOTH: You're a mermaid?

53:28.205 --> 53:30.924
Ariel, how nice of you to come.

53:31.375 --> 53:33.548
And you brought Flopper with you.

53:33.627 --> 53:35.254
The name's Flounder.

53:35.963 --> 53:37.010
Grrr!

53:37.089 --> 53:39.808
"Grrr" yourself, pipsqueak.

53:39.925 --> 53:41.848
Get that thing and hit me.

53:41.969 --> 53:44.392
One bite, and he's shrimp toast.

53:44.638 --> 53:47.517
Sweetheart, hand me my trident now.

53:48.434 --> 53:52.280
All this time, and you never told me?

53:52.354 --> 53:56.530
Kept the most important secret in
her whole life from her own daughter.

53:56.608 --> 53:59.111
Please, give it to me, Melody.

53:59.194 --> 54:01.413
No, hand it to me.

54:01.488 --> 54:04.583
- It's for your own good.
- She's lying!

54:04.658 --> 54:07.502
I've given you
what you've always wanted.

54:07.578 --> 54:11.128
She's the one who lied to you
all these years.

54:11.206 --> 54:14.176
- I was trying to protect you.
- By fencing me in?

54:14.501 --> 54:16.344
You knew how much I loved the sea.

54:16.587 --> 54:18.305
Why did you keep the truth from me?

54:18.380 --> 54:23.011
Melody, listen to me. If there was one
thing in my life that I could do over...

54:23.761 --> 54:25.308
Too late, Mom.

54:25.387 --> 54:26.434
Melody, no!

54:28.182 --> 54:29.525
(CACKLING)

54:34.396 --> 54:40.074
All the power of the seven seas
at my command!

54:42.696 --> 54:45.119
Hello! Can we get with the programme?

54:45.199 --> 54:47.452
It's still a small world down here!

54:49.495 --> 54:51.418
Mom!

54:51.497 --> 54:56.048
Your mommy was only trying
to protect you from <i>moi!</i>

54:56.126 --> 54:59.130
What she did, she did out of... (SNIFFS)

54:59.213 --> 55:00.556
...love.

55:01.882 --> 55:05.853
Little Melody's been a very naughty girl,

55:05.928 --> 55:09.478
stealing from her own grandfather.

55:09.681 --> 55:12.275
My grandfather?

55:12.559 --> 55:18.441
King Triton, ruler of Atlantica,
commander in chief of all of the oceans!

55:18.524 --> 55:22.495
Or at least he was,
until a certain little thief came along.

55:22.569 --> 55:23.570
You tricked me.

55:23.654 --> 55:26.407
You've got no one to blame but yourself.

55:27.658 --> 55:29.126
Tell me, Melody.

55:29.201 --> 55:32.296
Is being a mermaid
everything you dreamed?

55:32.412 --> 55:34.335
Was it worth it?

55:34.414 --> 55:35.882
(CACKLING)

55:36.416 --> 55:37.417
(GASPS)

55:37.543 --> 55:38.715
Oh!

55:38.919 --> 55:40.762
- (GROANS)
- Melody!

55:45.843 --> 55:48.346
Oh, and by the way,

55:48.428 --> 55:51.932
your time as a mermaid
has just about expired.

55:53.058 --> 55:54.355
Catch you later.

55:54.434 --> 55:57.358
I've got bigger fish to fry!

55:57.437 --> 56:00.111
Bigger fish! Now, there's an idea!

56:00.440 --> 56:01.817
(GRUNTING)

56:01.900 --> 56:03.652
We gotta keep trying.

56:05.445 --> 56:09.416
It's no use. It's too thick.

56:12.411 --> 56:14.630
(SOBBING) Oh, Flounder.

56:14.705 --> 56:17.299
I've ruined everything.

56:22.337 --> 56:25.261
We're guppies, man. Jellyfish.

56:25.340 --> 56:27.468
The great Tip and Dash.

56:27.634 --> 56:30.729
Cowards-slash-losers.

56:32.806 --> 56:35.355
Well, at least we're alive.

56:35.434 --> 56:39.029
Yeah, if you wanna call this living.

56:43.942 --> 56:45.569
Okay, on the one hand,

56:45.652 --> 56:47.825
we can live a long, healthy life,

56:47.946 --> 56:51.826
albeit as disgusting,
pathetic, cowardly...

56:52.034 --> 56:54.378
- Worms.
- That's good. Good.

56:54.453 --> 56:56.421
Cowardly worms.

56:56.496 --> 56:59.921
On the other hand, we could gather
our courage, if we had any,

57:00.042 --> 57:02.670
and storm the fortress and be heroes.

57:02.836 --> 57:06.181
Yeah, until they hack us up
into fish bait.

57:07.716 --> 57:09.764
You're right.

57:09.843 --> 57:11.265
(THUNDER CRACKING)

57:11.345 --> 57:12.346
(DASH GASPS)

57:12.429 --> 57:13.931
Melody's in there.

57:14.431 --> 57:18.937
She could be in big trouble.
She may really need our help!

57:19.019 --> 57:20.612
So what's it gonna be?

57:20.687 --> 57:23.156
A lifetime as worms,

57:23.231 --> 57:25.859
or two minutes as heroes?

57:25.943 --> 57:27.661
(CRACKING CONTINUES)

57:35.744 --> 57:40.045
All hail Queen Morgana!

57:41.041 --> 57:43.009
I'm hailin'! I'm hailin'!

57:44.461 --> 57:47.055
SCUTTLE: Hold on, sweetie!

57:47.130 --> 57:50.851
The cavalry is comin'!

57:51.677 --> 57:52.678
(GASPS)

